	"summary": "clevis bug fix and enhancement update",
	"details": "Clevis is a pluggable framework for automated decryption. It can be used to\nprovide automated decryption of data or even automated unlocking of LUKS\nvolumes. The clevis packages provide the client side of the Network Bound\nDisk Encryption (NBDE) project.\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* Server hangs in asking password unless user hits enter in clevis/dracut\n(BZ#2023256)",
